<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="416" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,790,1600,1627]" box="[151,790,1600,1627]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,790,1600,1627]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,790,1600,1627]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">
<taxonomicName box="[151,298,1601,1627]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Tetragonula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,298,1601,1627]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">Tetragonula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species of the “ 
<taxonomicName box="[492,601,1601,1627]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Trigona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laeviceps">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[492,601,1601,1627]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">laeviceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” species group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,1671,1804]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">
Members of this species group usually have a mesoscutum almost as evenly banded with hair as the “ 
<taxonomicName box="[1302,1423,1672,1696]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Trigona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="iridipennis">
<emphasis box="[1302,1423,1672,1696]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">iridipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” group, but these species are larger, with forewing length, including tegula, measuring between 
<number box="[1246,1281,1708,1732]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" value="4.2">4.2</number>
and 
<quantity box="[1341,1432,1708,1732]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" unit="mm" value="4.8">4.8 mm</quantity>
. Sakagami (
<number box="[279,337,1743,1767]" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" value="1978.0">1978</number>
) referred to this species group as the taxonomically most difficult group within 
<taxonomicName box="[1263,1399,1744,1768]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Tetragonula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1263,1399,1744,1768]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">Tetragonula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A single species has been reported in 
<collectingCountry box="[546,607,1780,1804]" name="India" pageId="15" pageNumber="416">India</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
